cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "Digital Registrar — Research"
abstract: >-
  Research stack for The Digital Registrar — a model-agnostic, resource-efficient
  AI framework for comprehensive cancer surveillance from pathology reports.
  Bundles the DSPy extraction pipeline, a doctor-facing annotation UI, a
  reproducible benchmark against GPT-4 / ClinicalBERT / rule-based extraction,
  and an ablation study of modular vs monolithic signatures.
